-- Friends Life posts 7 pct H1 drop in operating profit
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 02:24AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 6 (Reuters) - British insurer Friends Life Group <FLG.L> posted a 7 percent fall in first-half operating profit, weighed by a decline in the value of its new business.

The life and pensions group, created in 2008 by entrepreneur Clive Cowdery, said the fall in value had been expected, the result of changes to the pensions and savings business announced at the most recent budget.  Operating profit fell to 159 million pounds ($268.09 million) in the six months ended June 30, from 171 million pounds a year earlier.  The value of new business -